            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-02-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-02-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="306" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d306">
                <head ana="#head_untitled-missing-head-in-printed-volume">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Funchal,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-02-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 28, 1864</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Most Excellent Sir:</hi> In compliance with the orders
                    received from your excellency, I have intimated the commander of the war steamer
                    Florida to leave this port within twenty-four hours, and in reply to said
                    intimation I have received from said officer a communication, of which I have
                    the honor of transmitting a copy to your excellency, wherein the said commander
                    declares he was forced to come into this port in want of water, bread, and
                    coals, and that, consequently, it is impossible for him to quit this port
                    without those articles.</p>
                <p>Your excellency will decide whatever is just, and I await your excellency’s
                    orders on this head.</p>
                <p>God preserve your excellency.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JOAQUIN PEDRO DE CASTELBRANCO, <hi rend="italic">Post Captain R. N. and
                            Captain of the Port.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>His Excellency Dn. <hi rend="smallcaps">Jacintho Antonio Perdigao</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Civil Governor of the Funchal District.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
